    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-04T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/698: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-04T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1920—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. Changes in paragraphs 33 and 34 [of] articles regulating operations
                    International Court of Justice considered by Peruvian officials as throwing them
                    out of court. Secretary of Foreign Relations prepared cable to Peruvian
                    representatives in countries in League instructing them ask those Governments to
                    support request by Peru for appointment special commission consider Peru-Chile
                    case. At President’s request Minister consulted me before sending. I have
                    suggested delay for time to inquire if our Government is contemplating any move
                    to induce Chile agree arbitration. Please immediately [inform] and advise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
